AUTHORITY.Definition: the ability to influence other people and make them respect you, especially because you are confident or have a lot of knowledge

LEGITIMATE.Definition: allowed according to law, or reasonable and acceptable

FACILITATION.Definition: the process of making something possible or easier

CAPACITY.Definition: someone's ability to do a particular thing

DEMONS.Definition: a source or agent of evil, harm, distress, or ruin

TECHNICAL.Definition: relating to practical skills and methods that are used in a particular activity

IN GOOD SHAPE.Definition: in an original, normal, or fit condition

ESTABLISH.Definition: to start having a relationship with, or communicating with another person, company, country, or organization

LIKE-MINDED.Definition: people who are described as like-minded share the same opinions, ideas, or interests

LEAN ON.Definition: to use someone or something to help you, especially in a difficult situation

PROFITABLE.Definition: in a way that produces or is likely to produce an advantage

FORMIDABLE.Definition: causing you to have fear or respect for something or someone because that thing or person is large, powerful, or difficult

STEMMED.Definition: to be caused by (something or someone) : to come from (something or someone)

SCOPE.Definition: the range of a subject covered by a book, program, discussion, class, etc.

SCALE.Definition: to pattern, make, regulate, set, or estimate according to some rate or standard

CRITIQUE.Definition: to give an opinion or judgment about a piece or work, book, movie, etc.

INTENSIVE.Definition: involving a lot of effort or activity in a short period of time

BUILT-IN.Definition: included, made, or designed as part of something

INTELLECTUAL.Definition: relating to your ability to think and understand things, especially complicated ideas

ENTERPRISE.Definition: an organization, especially a business, or a difficult and important plan, especially one that will earn money

SEQUENCING.Definition: to combine things in a particular order, or discover the order in which they are combined

HIERARCHICAL.Definition: arranged according to people's or things' level of importance, or relating to such a system

ELEGANT.Definition: graceful and attractive in appearance or behavior

USER INTERFACE.Definition: the way in which the information on a computer, phone, etc. and instructions on how to use it are arranged on the screen and shown to the user

MASSIVE.Definition: very large in size, amount, or degree

QUIVER.Definition: a long, thin container for carrying arrows

AGGREGATE.Definition: something formed by adding together several amounts or things

OVERLAY.Definition: something such as a transparent layer or image that can be put over something else, for example to add information or show a relationship between two things

WIT.Definition: the ability to use words in a smart and humorous way

RADICAL.Definition: causing or being an example of great change; extreme

UNPREDICTABLE.Definition: likely to change suddenly and without reason and therefore not able to be predicted (= expected before it happens) or depended on

BETA.Definition: beta software is at the second stage of development

FALL APART.Definition: if an organization, system, or agreement falls apart, it fails or stops working effectively

ACADEMIC.Definition: relating to schools, colleges, and universities, or connected with studying and thinking, not with practical skills

KEY.Definition: very important and having a lot of influence on other people or things

REFINE.Definition: to make something pure or improve something, especially by removing unwanted material

DRIVING FORCES.Definition: someone or something that has the power to make things happen

OVERSTATED.Definition: to describe or explain something in a way that makes it seem more important or serious than it really is

REPETITIVELY.Definition: in a way that involves doing or saying the same thing several times, especially in a way that is boring

DICTATES.Definition: to influence something or make it necessary

COMBAT.Definition: to try to stop something unpleasant or harmful from happening or increasing

COGNITIVE BIASES.Definition: the way a particular person understands events, facts, and other people, which is based on their own particular set of beliefs and experiences and may not be reasonable or accurate

STRATEGICALLY.Definition: in a way that helps to achieve a plan, for example in business or politics

DIVERSIFY.Definition: to start to include more different types or things

PROLIFIC.Definition: producing a great number or amount of something

INTENDED.Definition: to have as a plan or purpose
